comments.text:
3:24 Those cute BROCCOLI TREES!
3:50 That's some heavy, unspoken heavy love
4:00 YEY!!! starry lights! (and potential stimming/OCD whatever that is but theclicking sounds is sooo comforting)
5:07 "I have it on TV all the time"
5:42 LOL the emergency cleaning feels so relatable 
6:51 Yey! that same dish (and broccoli trees) all the way to adulthood! I'm literally smelling the veggies, YEYYYYY
7:05 "Now, you can teach me how to cook" noooo, that like the greatest confession an autistic person 
8:17 We kind of can tell Carepackage feels it when he actually feels the CONNECTION/being relatedto or something, like intense emotional relief? like 16:22
9:05 That zoned out noise suppression works so well on them, how, I'm kind of jealous cuz I personally can't filter what I hear for most of the time
10:22 Non-ending analytical speech and vision board, that clearly feels like intense care and non-stopping tracking, which may feel like an obsession, dang he shows a lot of interest but could only express it that way (this feels very unintentional and it's hard to tell if not having experience with neurodivergent individual)
10:44 YEYYYYYYYYYY that half cooked egg yolk!!!!! And that noise suppression
16:52 Angel of mercy was that?
18:20 They're both trying so hard to find that connection where themselves feel it
21:57 Dang I actually enjoy that communication and theory presentation, 
22:45 Almonds/Amends, as an autistic non-native English speaker that resonates A LOT (English being a phonic language needs a lot more recognition ability than sematic languages, but needs less to uncompress for me personally, those energy requirements varies across individuals of all condition)
23:22 YeYYYYYYYYY!!!!!
26:53 Dang, I'm crying, that scene captures A LOT TO UNWRAP.  We really need that inspiration and the person who helps us to adapt expression, nice to see Braeburn being the role model for both Carepackage and Bottom/Split at 34:47 and 39:06. And Carepackage sure picks up how "protection" is expressed by Braeburn and reflects on his past actions for Bottom/Split) That happens and needs to happen for any individual to pick up a healthy way of thinking, especially when there is communitation difficulty for both party in a relationship. I don't exactly know how masking works, but introducing new thinking does help a lot when autistic couples/individuals gets trapped in deadend cycles. Glad to see the pair working through their own difficulty expressing feeling and come to more direct/verbal communitation. THANK YOU TAMERS FOR CAPRUTING THAT!!!!!!!!!!!
27:30 Wait, Arinos, is he related to that enlongated clown figure from last movie's ending?
29:14 Sooooarin!
30:40 "Nope, too organized for that"
32:33 Thank you for capturing that eye look
33:19 Solidified speech bubble, words weighs, and neurodivergent sensory blast bzzz
33:26 Notice how the juggling surpasses the sun like a solar eclipse?
33:44 Nice screen saver worth background!!! That feel like a a lot of fun (putting together this image)
34:15 Carepackage trying sooo hard to feel and relate, that's kind of gold
34:30 "but, I did that for you" Including that whole long ass study and research, info compilation and presentation that bottom/split didn't felt interested in. Dang this brings me to tears
34:50 That happens when people value different things, not on the same frequency, having trouble with understanding, or hyperfocused/masking to make things right. But we can tell Carepackage has been growing empathy and great care for Bottom/Split. 
35:12 THE AUTISTIC PONY SHOWING HIS EMOTION AND VULNERABILITY!!!!
35:24 Does that mean Carepackage gets turned on when he sees his loved one starting to take control of his own life? And that he feels happy for Bottom/Split growing out of helplessness and gains autonomy? So sweet!!!
35:36 TAKE NOTE OF THAT, writing things down in advance to therapy works
36:23 Happy healthy boundaries!
37:12 when you can't filter your double empathy and random stuff you pick up, and that eventually devours your own thought
38:01 38:18 38:35 40:35 43:45 The hope born from painful, unspoken, and unprocessed love
39:23 Yeyyyy!!! FAMILY!!! Glad to see Bottom/Split caring about Braeburn and expressing care and nice wishes!
39:34 PIZZA!
40:50 Carepackage does seem well contained for most of the time and doesn't let his past step over him like 43:02, makes sense how he picks up the "chains" and insecurity of Soarin. Remember that Shining Armour could do the same.
44:15 Notice how other couples fade from the picture, and now it's Bic Mac's turn to work things out. 44:43, He does feel like a good father, which Bic Mac didn't have.
45:05 With Arinos popping out in the scene, we see how Carepackage gains more understanding and close up observation, AND HE SMILES!!! Does that mean he started to feel more as he gains more indepth understanding? (which is an adaptation process for some neurodivergent peopleto go through) Or does that mean, they have a child!!! Oh and Bottom/Split annoyed but trying to figure out what has been engraved in his own body and mind, golden.
47:05 POTENTIAL BREAKTHROUGH FOR RARITY!

Again many many thanks to Tamers and the community, sorry got all brain venting or something. But we see, cherish and appreciate, and trying our best to get the most out of what you're expressing non-directly/verbally. We cherish it (sorry fucked up mind)
